28.body:
$ git pull # sync
$ git checkout Deliverable-1 # in Deliverable-1 local branch, git log see more info
$ git branch test-branch # create a test1 branch locally, git log see more info
$ git checkout test-branch # at test-branch locally, git log see more info
$ # make some changes in test1
$ git add all; git commit -ma "Test Done" # A new local commit point created say B, git log see more info
$ git checkout Deliverable-1 # at Deliverable-1 local branch, git log see more info
$ git merge test-branch # merge Deliverable-1 from test-branch
$ # solve conflicts
$ # merge sucessful, git log see more info
$ git push # git log shows: HEAD -> Deliverable-1, origin/Deliverable-1, test-branch

34.body: Change term "base note" to "key signature" (in note and interval mode) Change "Hamburger Menu" to "Left Menu" Change "S" to "F" ("Custom Setting" Button -> "Filter" Button)
34.title: Terminology Changes

35.body: "mentronome" toggle to toggle mentronome in song practice mode "error allowance" can select 10 levels of error allowance, the higher the level, the more accurate sound the user is supposed to produce "in-app volume" as name suggested "theme", defalt simplistic ( Can have "PPAP" theme, "Black Mode" theme, "50 Shades of Grey" theme (for color bind people), ... )
35.title: Setting Menu

37.body: The text (above note in note mode and interval mode, right to notes in chord mode) will have 6 states, namely "..." (please sing), "↑" (little low), "↑↑" (too low), "✓" (just right), "↓" (little high), "↓↓" (too high) Add "Setting Menu", "More Menu" button which can be found in "Left Menu"
37.title: General Changes

38.body: "A" button for select/unselect all, "C" button for select complement Slider is the entire page instead of the "notes set" box, so that user can see more notes
38.title: Filter Changes

39.body: text right beside notes will also displays up/downarrows or checkmarks
